{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=2008 |Team=South Carolina Gamecocks |Image=South Carolina Gamecocks wordmark.svg |ImageSize=150 |Conference=Southeastern Conference |Division=Eastern Division |ShortConference=SEC |Record=7-6 |ConfRecord=4-4 |CoachRank= |APRank= |BCSRank= |HeadCoach=[[Steve Spurrier]] |DefCoach=[[Ellis Johnson (American football coach)|Ellis Johnson]] |OScheme= |DScheme= |StadiumArena=[[Williams-Brice Stadium]] (c. 80,250, grass) |Champion= |BowlTourney=[[2009 Outback Bowl|Outback Bowl]] vs. [[2008 Iowa Hawkeyes football team|Iowa]] |BowlTourneyResult=L 31-10 }} {{2008 SEC football standings}} The '''2008 South Carolina Gamecocks football team''' represented the [[University of South Carolina]] in the [[college football]] [[2008 NCAA Division I FBS football season|season of 2008-2009]]. The team's head football coach was [[Steve Spurrier]], who served his fourth season at USC. The Gamecocks played their home games at [[Williams-Brice Stadium]] in [[Columbia, South Carolina]].
==Preseason== Carolina had their first spring practice on March 21, 2008. It was the first of 15 spring practice sessions for the Gamecocks, who return 54 lettermen in Steve Spurrier's fourth season. The annual Garnet & Black Spring Game is scheduled for 1:00 p.m., Saturday, April 19.
